{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"compacted_at":1784254312255757667,"compiled_state":{"alias":"interfaith-proud-dromedary","assignee":"Joe Oakhart","attestations":{"plan-review":{"algorithm":"sshsig","author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","envelope":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.opcert.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","head_sha":"6b25dbead186639a436b1d5faf7cb03e99001efc","key_id":null,"kind":"plan-review","manifest":["plan-review: PASS","ticket: 6642-814b-8bc5-4ff4","material: 2d725a3c3b0fcf63","model: claude-sonnet-4-6","runner: pydantic_ai","blocking: 0","advisory: 9","rebar-version: 0.7.1 (6b25dbead)","regver: b293b9a55de591cc","verified-at-sha:2165ee5cf60d83451c602a58cc7cd21619cb3b24","dep absent AGENTS.md","dep cefa7b90761f53680fb7cb081ce9f55dd20c16094c572a56dab975068a915215 CLAUDE.md"],"material_fingerprint":"2d725a3c3b0fcf63","merged_log_commit":"2165ee5cf60d83451c602a58cc7cd21619cb3b24","principal":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","signature":null,"signed_at":1784238485562564000}},"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","authorship":{"signed":4,"unsigned":6},"authorship_ledger":[{"content_hash":"92d138151cb8c37c374f23aef08fa55c90c6b2c76c1d5af69cee47a2a8c00de3","event_uuid":"70e9d634-699d-4c2c-965e-f64d4b232518","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784238485563034001-70e9d634-699d-4c2c-965e-f64d4b232518"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"3ee5ad20122313e7be7ca2788ac4cde83b77b33e38c19814f2dcd330f2b2d34e","event_uuid":"97b7dc9e-3b3d-4206-844f-c95f5c113689","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784252664083006001-97b7dc9e-3b3d-4206-844f-c95f5c113689"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"ba9c351fd1126ec3fda06162052981ae908742cc08e032d7bb24cf9255cd7f76","event_uuid":"f625b7ff-e4be-4a47-9754-ce0560d8eb79","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784252664347621001-f625b7ff-e4be-4a47-9754-ce0560d8eb79"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"b4a8ff13302d962b36d0b7840f870d021e2d6223ac31b8bba7520cf3ec17200c","event_uuid":"a40c303c-69c9-4f21-880e-aa87153845a6","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784254312255757666-a40c303c-69c9-4f21-880e-aa87153845a6"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-212_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"aa9cb5ff-3fdb-44d3-8af8-c125c27f20ad","comments":[],"created_at":1784230954088867001,"deps":[{"link_uuid":"5f7861a5-9ff1-4569-8f14-4c7691f22952","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"073d-51d8-3e58-4b14"}],"description":"# Create canonical AGENTS.md (rebar dev guide) + reduce CLAUDE.md to a thin @AGENTS.md pointer\n\n## Why\n\n`AGENTS.md` is read natively by Codex, Cursor, Copilot's coding agent, Zed, Windsurf, Amp,\nFactory, Jules, Devin, RooCode, and Cline — so one canonical `AGENTS.md` covers the ecosystem,\nand Claude Code is bridged by a one-line import. This also fixes the size/duplication\nanti-pattern: sections that duplicate a `docs/` file become one-line pointers.\n\n## What\n\nAuthor a lean `AGENTS.md` at the repo root that keeps rebar-INTERNAL developer specifics inline\nand replaces every already-documented topic with a one-line `docs/…md` pointer. Then reduce\n`CLAUDE.md` to a single `@AGENTS.md` import plus an optional `## Claude Code` section.\n\n- **INLINE (kept in full):** intro; the record-work/claim-before-you-work operating rules; the\n  parallel-agent loop; env bootstrap (`make install`/`make hooks`); module-size policy; Serena\n  navigation; a **condensed** Git/Gerrit section; a 6-line library snippet.\n- **POINTER (one line each), to EXISTING docs:** gate protocols → `docs/plan-review-gate.md`;\n  quality gates + ticket template + project criteria → `docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md`; MCP\n  tool set → `docs/mcp-reference.md`; store-shares-writes + parent-first cascade →\n  `docs/concurrency.md`; ticket model → `docs/ticket-model.md` (created by S1); session logs →\n  `docs/event-schema.md` + `docs/user-guide.md`; library reference → `docs/reuse-surface.md`; the\n  LLM agent-operations topic → `docs/llm-framework.md`; the completion close-gate →\n  `docs/plan-review-gate.md`. These are POINTERS only — this story writes no content into those\n  docs (their content already exists; the two \"stowaway\" topics currently mixed into CLAUDE.md's\n  Session-logs heading are simply not carried into AGENTS.md).\n\n## Scope\n\nIn: new `AGENTS.md`, rewritten `CLAUDE.md`. No writes to any `docs/*` file (pointers only). Out:\n`CLAUDE.local.md` (S3), the shim/reference sweep (S6), and code. **Depends on S1** (already linked\n`depends_on`): `docs/ticket-model.md` must exist before `AGENTS.md` points at it. Rollback is a\nplain `git revert` (docs/text only).\n\n## Design decisions (spike-validated)\n\n- The `@AGENTS.md` import is PROVEN in Claude Code 2.1.211 (headless canary + official docs\n  recommend exactly `@AGENTS.md` + `## Claude Code`); no symlink fallback.\n- Imports \"load at launch\" and do not reduce context, so the token win comes from de-dup into docs\n  and **AGENTS.md must itself be lean.** A grounded estimate puts a complete lean file at ~152\n  lines and ≤ 200 only if the Git/Gerrit section is condensed to agent-actionable rules and defers\n  the full recipe to `CONTRIBUTING.md` (verbatim Gerrit → ~215-230, which misses the target).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `AGENTS.md` exists at repo root and is ≤ 200 lines.\n  - Proving: `test -f AGENTS.md && [ \"$(wc -l < AGENTS.md)\" -le 200 ]`\n- [ ] The Git/Gerrit section is condensed (≤ ~55 lines) and defers the full recipe to\n  `CONTRIBUTING.md`.\n  - Proving: `rg -q 'CONTRIBUTING.md' AGENTS.md`; reviewer confirms the section ≤ 55 lines.\n- [ ] Each already-documented topic is a one-line pointer, not a restated section.\n  - Proving: `rg -n 'docs/plan-review-gate.md|docs/mcp-reference.md|docs/ticket-model.md|docs/concurrency.md|docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md|docs/llm-framework.md' AGENTS.md`\n- [ ] Every `docs/…md` path that `AGENTS.md` points at resolves to a real file (no dangling\n  pointer; targets created by S1 are in place by then).\n  - Proving: `for p in $(rg -o 'docs/[A-Za-z0-9_-]+\\.md' AGENTS.md | sort -u); do test -f \"$p\" || { echo \"MISSING $p\"; exit 1; }; done`\n- [ ] `CLAUDE.md` is a single `@AGENTS.md` import + optional `## Claude Code` section, ≤ 30 lines.\n  - Proving: `[ \"$(rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md)\" = 1 ] && [ \"$(wc -l < CLAUDE.md)\" -le 30 ]`\n- [ ] `make lint` passes.\n  - Proving: `make lint`","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"AGENTS.md","reason":"new canonical dev guide"},{"path":"CLAUDE.md","reason":"reduce to @AGENTS.md pointer"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","073d-51d8-3e58-4b14"],["parent","81e2-ad5e-bfe2-4653"]],"parent_id":"81e2-ad5e-bfe2-4653","parent_status_uuid":"97b7dc9e-3b3d-4206-844f-c95f5c113689","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"6642-814b-8bc5-4ff4","ticket_type":"story","title":"Create canonical AGENTS.md (rebar dev guide) + reduce CLAUDE.md to a thin @AGENTS.md pointer","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["d871c0f8-12bf-429f-b8af-315fc47eac4a","5f7861a5-9ff1-4569-8f14-4c7691f22952","6d9ea785-9e4b-4d1e-9f0a-350fb2aacb1f","b5390584-64f6-4847-98cc-df1a23ada60c","045f68c5-2cc8-4f1c-9b42-d43d0c5add96","4f2a9d2a-045f-4476-9b30-b0f94a256646","70e9d634-699d-4c2c-965e-f64d4b232518","97b7dc9e-3b3d-4206-844f-c95f5c113689","f625b7ff-e4be-4a47-9754-ce0560d8eb79","a40c303c-69c9-4f21-880e-aa87153845a6"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784254312255757667,"uuid":"c737c1d6-8e33-4050-bd75-ee6e5f204bb7"}